article.headline: UNC Greensboro 65, Georgia Southern 62
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Kyle Hines scored a game-high 20 points to help UNC Greensboro sneak by Georgia Southern 65-62 on Monday night. Ricky Hickman added 15 points and Kevin Oleksiak finished with 10 points for the Spartans (12-9, 9-2 Southern Conference), who won their sixth-straight conference game. Georgia Southern (10-11, 3-7) led 38-37 at the break, but UNC pushed ahead in the second half. Both teams had more turnovers than field goals. Donte Gennie led four Georgia Southern players in double figures with 12 points, while Louis Graham had a double-double with 11 points and a game-high 13 rebounds. Jimmy Tobias and Dwayne Foreman added 10 points each, while Foreman hit 2-for-3 from beyond the arc.
